public class BusObject_mxJPO
extends AbstractPropertyObject_mxJPO

The class is used to export, create, delete and update business objects within MX.

getMxNames

public Set<String> getMxNames(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
                       throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Searches for all business object of current type definition and returns all MX names. The revision of the business object is appended to the name of the business object split by SPLIT_NAME. If types which are derived from original type are used, the type is the prefix of the name with the prefix SPLIT_TYPE.

Specified by:
getMxNames in class AbstractObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Returns:
set of found business object names (and revision)
Throws:
matrix.util.MatrixException - if the query for all business objects for given type failed

extractMxName

public String extractMxName(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                            File _file)
                     throws UpdateException_mxJPO
Extracts the MX name from given file name if the file prefix and suffix matches. If the file prefix and suffix not matches a null is returned. If the type definition has derived types and the extracted name does not include the the type, the business type is added.

Overrides:
extractMxName in class AbstractObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_file - file for which the MX name is searched
Returns:
MX name or null if the file is not an update file for current type definition
Throws:
UpdateException_mxJPO - if the configuration item name could not be extracted from the file name

matchMxName

public boolean matchMxName(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           String _mxName,
                           String _match)
Checks if given MX name without prefix and suffix matches given match string. The MX name is split with SPLIT_NAME to get the name and revision of the business object. A MX name matches if the business object name or revision matches.

Overrides:
matchMxName in class AbstractObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_mxName - name (and revision) of the administration business object
_match - string which must be matched
Returns:
true if the given MX name matches; otherwise false

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to
  • reset the description
  • set the version and author attribute
  • reset all not ignored attributes
  • define the TCL variable "OBJECTID" with the object id of the represented business object
The original method of the super class if called surrounded with a history off, because if the update itself is done the modified basic attribute and the version attribute of the business object is updated.
The new generated MQL code is set in the front of the already defined MQL code in _preMQLCode and appended to the MQL statements in _postMQLCode.

Overrides:
update in class AbstractPropertyObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update executed within derived class failed
